<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Dismissed S. Korean Coach Cha Takes Chinese league Team </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 16 (Xinhua) -- South Korean World Cup coach Cha
Bum Kun was announced manager of Chinese first division side Shen
Zhen Ping'an on Friday.
</P>
<P>
It came as a surprise that Cha, fired after a 0-5 humiliation
by the Netherlands in their second world Cup group match, took
charge of a newly-promoted Chinese league team.
</P>
<P>
South Korea crashed to a 1-3 opening round defeat by Mexico
before Cha's dismission and finally managed a 1-1 draw with
Belgium in their last match without Cha.
</P>
<P>
Shout Korea, co-host with Japan for the 2002 World Cup, has
never won a match and qualified for the second round in all their
recent three World Cup appearances. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
