</P>
<P>
South Korean soldiers broke the aerial of the submarine and
pulled it for a long time before it sank, he said, adding that the
crewmen "had no alternative but to kill themselves," as they were
unable to send out distress signals. (DPRK-SKorea-Submarine)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
PHNOM PENH -- One of Cambodia's opposition leaders, Sam Rainsy,
appeals to the government Wednesday for demilitarization of
election process and neutrality of police and military forces
during the July 26 elections.
</P>
<P>
"Aware of an increase in military movement in various parts of
Cambodia, the Sam Rainsy Party appeals to the present government
to allow the electoral process to proceed without violence,
intimidation or involvement of military and police forces in the
electoral process," Sam Rainsy said.
