All sides should not use troops for partisan political
purposes, and all military and police forces should be loyal to
the nation instead of any political party or political leader, the
president of Sam Rainsy Party said. (Cambodia-Sam Rainsy-Appeal)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
LONDON -- The Britain government welcomed on Thursday what it
described as "signals" that the Irish Republican Army may be about
to decommission its weapons.
</P>
<P>
A government spokesman said the IRA accepted that
decommissioning was an indispensable part of the Northern Ireland
peace agreement reached last April.
</P>
<P>
But he denied newspaper reports which said arrangements for a
hand-over had already been made.
</P>
<P>
"There have been signals that we welcome. There are signals
that they are aware of the importance of decommissioning," he
said. (UK-IRA-Decommissioning Arms) 
</P>
