<HEADLINE> French Prime Minister to Visit Britain Next Week </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 16 (Xinhua) -- French Prime Minister Lionel Jospin
will pay a visit to Britain on Thursday and Friday next week, said
the press service of the Matignon prime minister's office on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
This will be another image-building diplomatic move by the
prime minister after his successful visit to the United States in
June.
</P>
<P>
Jospin will address the Royal Society for the Arts in London on
the European construction and Franco-British relations at the
invitation of British Foreign Secretary Robin Cook.
</P>
<P>
He will visit the county of Durham, which is the home to the
constituency of Prime Minister Tony Blair.  
</P>
