<HEADLINE> China Backs International Conference on Mideast </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, July 16 (Xinhua) -- China backs the Egyptian-French
initiative to hold an international conference to rescue the
Middle East peace process, Chinese Ambassador to Egypt Yang
Fuchang said.
</P>
<P>
Egypt's Middle East News Agency Thursday quoted Yang as saying
in an interview that China's support to the Palestinians and their
cause is firm and will never be changed.
</P>
<P>
During Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu's visit to
Beijing at the end of May, Chinese leaders urged him to carry out
the commitments made in the signed peace accords and
unconditionally accept the U.N. Resolution 425 calling for an
Israeli withdrawal from south Lebanon, the ambassador said.
</P>
<P>
Yang said that the Mideast peace process is facing a collapse
due to Israel's intransigence.
</P>
<P>
The Palestinian-Israeli talks have been stalled for about 16
months, while a number of countries are discussing the idea to
hold an international conference on the peace process as jointly
proposed by Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak and his French
counterpart Jacques Chirac.
</P>
<P>
Praising the healthy development of the Egyptian-Chinese trade
relations, the Chinese ambassador said the level of trade exchange
rose to 520 million U.S. dollars last year, of which 50 million
dollars were in Egyptian exports.
</P>
<P>
He said both countries are now looking into the establishment
of an economic and industrial zone in East Suez. China will invest
7 million dollars in the zone, he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
