<HEADLINE> Another Chinese Medical Team Expected in Ethiopia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, July 16 (Xinhua) -- A protocol concerning the
assignment of the 10th Chinese medical team to work in Ethiopia
was signed here Thursday between the governments of China and
Ethiopia.
</P>
<P>
According to the agreement, the new incoming 15-person 10th
Chinese medical team will render its service in Nazareth
Hospital, 90 kms away from the capital Addis Ababa, like its
preceding team for a period of two years.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government will provide Ethiopian side, on grant
basis, with part of medical apparatus and instruments including
acupuncture instruments under the care and to be used by the
Chinese medical team in Nazareth Hospital.
</P>
<P>
Ethiopian Vice-Minister of Economic Development and
Cooperation Mulatu Teshome and Chinese Ambassador to Ethiopia
Jiang Zhengyun attended the signing ceremony.
</P>
<P>
The first Chinese medical team was sent to Ethiopia in 1974.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the two governments Thursday also sealed a pact on
using 108 million Renminbi Yuan (13 million U.S. Dollars) of
interest free loan, from balance of previous agreements of
economic and technical cooperation, for the construction of Addis
Ababa ring road. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
