<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Fish Export Earns Ghana $95m in 1997 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, July 16 (Xinhua) -- Ghana earned 95 million U.S.
Dollars from fish export in 1997, a report from Accra said
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The report, quoting Deputy Trade and Industry Minister Dan
Abodakpi as the source, said the amount accounted for 28.5
percent of Ghana's total non-traditional exports last year.
</P>
<P>
Abodakpi made the remarks at a three-day workshop organized by
the African, Caribbean and Pacific States (APC) and the European
Union (EU) aimed at expanding fishing sector exports.
</P>
<P>
Eleven Ghanaian companies and nine freezer vessels have been
certified to export fishing products following an EU ruling in
June admitting imports from the West African country, the report
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
