<HEADLINE> Annan Recommends Extending Mandate of UNPREDEP </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, July 16 (Xinhua) -- U.N. Secretary-General Kofi
Annan on Thursday recommended to extend the mandate of the United
Nations Preventive Deployment Force (UNPREDEP)in the former
Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia for a further period of six months
until February 28, 1999.
</P>
<P>
Annan also recommended to increase the strength of the military
observer and the civilian police of UNPREDEP by an additional 12
and 24 personnel respectively.
</P>
<P>
In his report to the Security Council of the United Nations,
the U.N. Secretary-General said the peace and stability in the
former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia continues to depend largely
on development in other parts of the region.
</P>
<P>
Annan said that recent developments in Kosovo have highlighted
the danger of renewed violence in the area and the serious
repercussions such violence could have upon the external and
internal security of the Republic.  
</P>
</TEXT>
