<HEADLINE> Venerable Islamic Figure Passes Away </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 17 (Xinhua) -- Imam al-Haj Salah An Shiwei,
president of the Islamic Association of China, passed away on
Tuesday in Beijing and funeral service in line with Islamic
tradition was held to mourn the well-known Islamic figure.
</P>
<P>
Li Ruihuan, chairman of the National Committee of the Chinese
People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC), and a number
of other high-ranking officials offered their condolences to the
family.
</P>
<P>
Leading officials and representatives from the United Front
Work Department of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of
China (CPC), the State Ethnic Affairs Commission, the State Bureau
of Religious Affairs and the Islamic Association of China attended
today's funeral, along with Beijing's religious leaders and
numerous Muslim representatives.
</P>
<P>
An Shiwei, born 1919, was an influential figure in religious
circle both at home and abroad. He started working for the Islamic
Association of China in 1956 and had served as a member and
Standing Committee member of the CPPCC National Committee since
1978. He offered decades of contributions to China's religious
freedom, national unity and social stability.  
