<HEADLINE> Share Prices Rose Sharply on Singapore Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, July 17 (Xinhua) --Share prices continued to rise on
Singapore Stock Market Friday as the benchmark Straits Times
Industrials Index (STII) climbed by 21.13 points to close at
1095.10 points.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said share prices rose from morning session and closed
sharply higher on the back of strong regional currencies led by
the Japanese yen.
</P>
<P>
Thursday's record gains on Wall Street also gave sentiment a
boost and bolstered the rise, they said.
</P>
<P>
They noted that market also applauded the IMF's approval of an
immediate one billion-U.S. dollar disbursement from its bailout
package and the agreement by the beleaguered country's major
creditors to reschedule its sovereign debt.
</P>
<P>
The total turnover shot up to 205.07 million shares from
Thursday's 90.96 million units while the market value of the
traded shares surged to 325.49 Singapore dollars (192,60 U.S.
dollars) from the 196.61 million Singapore dollars (116.43 million
U.S. dollars) on Thursday. Advances outstripped declines sharply
by 266 to 48 while 276 stocks remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
MBF Cap was the most active stock as it ended on a turnover of
17.70 million units. It was followed by M Res which had 15.65
million counters done. SingTel was next with 9.31 million shares
changing hands.
</P>
<P>
Creative 50 was the biggest gainer as it gained 60 cents to
finish at 21.50 Singapore dollars. SIA F edged up 35 cents to end
at 8.65 Singapore dollars. Thai pr inched by 30 cents to close at
3.32 U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, Rothmans 200 topped the losers of the day as
it fell by 70 cents to end at 11.90 Singapore dollars. CenProp
shed 30 cents to finish at 9.20 Singapore dollars. OUT f was down
15 cents to close at 1.25 Singapore dollars. 
</P>
