<HEADLINE> Senior EU Official Encourages Baltic Efforts to Join EU </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, July 17 (Xinhua) -- A senior official of the European
Union (EU) encouraged on Friday Latvia and Lithuania on their
efforts to join the regional bloc.
</P>
<P>
European Commissioner for External Affairs Hans van den Broek
said the two Baltic countries had already made great strides
toward EU membership.
</P>
<P>
However, van den Broek said before his scheduled visit to
Latvia and Lithuania next week, "they both know that much more
needs to be done."
</P>
<P>
"The date of accession is in their hands," he added, "and the
quicker they implement the necessary rules and reforms, the
quicker they will join (the union)."
</P>
<P>
The commissioner said he would tell the two governments that
the European Commission, as the EU's executive arm, is fully
committed to doing everything in its power to speed up the
accession process.
</P>
<P>
In addition, he would welcome the improved economic performance
in both Latvia and Lithuania and their efforts to adopt and
implement EU rules and practices.
</P>
<P>
From among 11 candidate countries, the European Union has
invited Poland, Hungary, the Czech Republic, Romania, Slovenia and
Cyprus to start accession talks. 
</P>
