<HEADLINE> Shenzhen Airport Assisting Chek Lap Kok </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, July 17 (Xinhua) -- Foreign flight crews engaged in
transport of cargo bound for Hong Kong will be exempted of
entry/exit visas when transiting the Shenzhen Airport due to
temporary freight handling difficulties at Chek Lap Kok, the
special administratives region's new airport.
</P>
<P>
Officials with the Shenzhen General Immigration and Customs
Office explained relaxation of requirements as a move to improve
efficiency.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Public Security has granted the general port of
entry approval to simplify customs clearance procedures.
Beginning yesterday, ports of entry at the Futian and Shenzhen
airports initiated round-the-clock customs clearance services.
</P>
<P>
Shenzhen Airport, which feature a parking apron covering
290,000 sq.m., is fully prepared to handle foreign cargo flights
and all cargo transfered from Chek Lap Kok.
</P>
<P>
Korean Airlines was the first foreign air freight company to
suggest that Shenzhen Airport be used as a temporary handling
facility for Chek Lap Kok. The Korean company will reroute four
cargo flights from Seoul to Shenzhen beginning on July 23.
</P>
<P>
Sources with the Shenzhen Airport (Group) Company said that all
service fees for foreign cargo flights will be paid by concerned
air freight transportation companies after the evacuation work is
completed, and related fees will be at or below levels charged at
Chek Lap Kok.
</P>
<P>
Concerned agents and companies engaged in air freight transport
will not be required to pay extra fees at the Shenzhen Airport.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
