<HEADLINE> 16 Die in Traffic Accident in Nepal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, July 17 (Xinhua) -- At least 16 people died and 14
others seriously injured Friday morning when a passenger bus fell
150 meters off the road in Piuthan District, mid-western Nepal,
the official RSS news agency said.
</P>
<P>
The injured have been admitted to the local hospital and the
police is investigating into the cause of the accident, RSS said.
</P>
<P>
A total of 62 people have died in traffic accidents in the
country since June 22. 
</P>
</TEXT>
