<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 40th Anniversary of Sino-Cambodia Ties Marked </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, July 17 (Xinhua) -- China and Cambodia called for
efforts to further strengthen the Sino-Cambodia relations here
Friday at a reception held to mark the 40th anniversary of the
establishment of diplomatic relations between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Friday's ceremony came just nine days before Cambodia will have
a National Assembly elections.
</P>
<P>
More than 200 guests from the Royal Government of Cambodia,
representatives of overseas Chinese and enterprises in Cambodia
attended the reception. Among those present at the reception are
also some senior officials of Cambodian Government.
</P>
<P>
Cambodia's Co-Premiers Ung Hout and Hun Sen had earlier sent
their congratulatory letters to Chinese Premier Zhu Rongji and
Foreign Minister Tang Jiaxuan.
</P>
<P>
At the reception, hosted by Chinese Embassy to Cambodia, Yan
Tingai, Chinese Ambassador and Sok An, Co-Minister of the
Cambodian Cabinet, spoke highly of the all-round development of
the Sino-Cambodia relations over the past 40 years.
</P>
<P>
China and Cambodia formally established diplomatic relations on
July 19, 1958. 
</P>
</TEXT>
