<HEADLINE> Museveni Outlines Causes for Africa's </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, July 17 (Xinhua) -- Ugandan President Yoweri Museveni
has outlined the causes leading to the European colonization of
Africa and hence the backwardness of the continent.
</P>
<P>
He made the analysis in a speech delivered Friday morning at
the closing ceremony of the first national congress of the ruling
National Resistance Movement.
</P>
<P>
The president said the lack of power, unity, science and
technology as well as small population are among the main factors
that result in the European colonization of the whole continent.
</P>
<P>
He gave special emphasis to the tribal system in the
continent, noting that it is this system that separated the
different ethnic groups and kept them from being united as a
whole.
</P>
<P>
China and Japan were cited as examples of unity in front of
European enemies.
</P>
<P>
He called on all ethnic groups in Uganda to be united together
and progress together.
</P>
<P>
The five-day conference is the first of its kind in Ugandan
history. At the meeting, Museveni was elected unopposed the
chairperson of the Movement on Monday.
</P>
<P>
A total of 1,554 representatives of the Movement from across
the country attended the national conference at which they
reached resolutions on security, national unity, agricultural
modernization and some other issues. 
</P>
</TEXT>
