<BODY>
<HEADLINE> BHP Products Output Up in June </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, July 17 (Xinhua) -- Australia's leading company, the
Broken Hill Proprietary (BHP) Co. Ltd., said Friday its copper
concentrate and raw steel output recorded a two-digit increase in
June.
</P>
<P>
Copper concentrate production reached 58,900 tons in June, up
17 percent from the same period of 1997 and its total raw steel
production was 731,000 tons, 11 percent higher than that reported
for the same month last year, the company said in its monthly
production report.
</P>
<P>
Production and shipments of copper concentrate rose because of
the resumption of normal production at Ok Tedi copper mine in
Papua New Guinea following a period of unseasonably dry weather,
the diversified miner said.
</P>
<P>
Oil and condensate production rose 10 percent in June to 6.23
million barrels, compared to the same time last year.
</P>
<P>
Natural gas production remained steady at 21.1 billion cubic
feet (594 million cubic meter) compared to the previous
corresponding 21.2 billion cubic feet (600 million cubic meter).
</P>
<P>
Iron ore production rose 4 percent to 4.50 million tons,
compared to the previous corresponding month's 4.33 million tons.
</P>
<P>
Production of manganese has dropped to 134,000 tons, compared
to 192,000 tons, due to a market downturn and some maintenance
work.
</P>
<P>
Ferroalloy production fell to 17,000 tons, compared to 20,000
tons.
</P>
<P>
Coal production was 1.799 million tons in June, marginally
lower than the same month last year because of weather and
equipment availability.
</P>
<P>
BHP's production of silver in concentrate in June was 1.14
million ounces.
</P>
<P>
Platinum in concentrate production was 1.36 million ounces.
</P>
<P>
Production at BHP's Cannington silver mine in Queensland,
Australia, and the Hartley platinum mine in Zimbabwe began in
October last year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
