<HEADLINE> Chinese Vice-Premier Meets BIS Chairman </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 17 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-Premier Wen Jiabao
met here today with Alfons Verplaetse, chairman of the board of
directors of the Bank for International Settlements (BIS).
</P>
<P>
Wen congratulated BIS on the establishment of its Asian-Pacific
office in Hong Kong last week.
</P>
<P>
"Establishment of the office shows that BIS attaches great
importance to Asia, especially China, since the Hong Kong office
is the first the bank has opened outside its headquarters in the
Swiss city of Basle," said Wen.
</P>
<P>
Wen expressed hope that BIS will play an active role in
promoting the financial stability and economic development in Asia.
</P>
<P>
BIS, an international financial institution established in
1930, is comprised of 45 central banks and monetary authorities,
including the People's Bank of China (PBOC). BIS is devoted to
strengthening ties among central banks, while at the same time
enhancing the central bank's supervision and management over
financial agencies.
</P>
<P>
PBOC Governor Dai Xianglong was present at the meeting.
</P>
</TEXT>
