<HEADLINE> College Graduates Should Qualify for Social Needs: </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 17 (Xinhua) -- Administrative Secretary Anson
Chan of the Hong Kong Administrative Region said here Friday that
the SAR government hopes the college graduates of Hong Kong would
qualify for the demand of the society.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the graduation ceremony of the Intensified Learning
Opportunity Program of the University of Hong Kong, Chan said the
annual investment of the SAR government in higher education is 13
billion HK dollars (1.7 billion U.S. dollars), about one-third of
the government's total investment in education.
</P>
<P>
Chan said the society needs talents who are able to think
independently, have world vision, can analyze matters from a
overall perspective, and stand ready to take responsibilities.
</P>
<P>
Thirty second-year full-time students from the Faculty of
Social Sciences or School of Business of the University of Hong
Kong have taken part in the 16-month program.
</P>
<P>
The 30 students have taken part in activities including
personal growth and leadership development, socio-cultural
research as well as business-oriented course. 
</P>
</TEXT>
