<HEADLINE> Pro-Poor Housing Program Tops Estrada's Agenda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, July 17 (Xinhua) -- Philippine President Joseph Estrada
has proposed the establishment of a guarantee fund for housing
which he expects to be set up within his first 100 days in office.
</P>
<P>
The fund, which will provide poor families with long-term,
affordable credit to own decent dwellings, forms part of Estrada's
first 100 days' People's Priority Agenda to be presented to
Congress on July 27, a news release from the Presidential Palace
said Friday.
</P>
<P>
Aside from the establishment of a guarantee fund, the Estrada
administration's strategy in dealing with the housing problem also
includes the participation of the private sector in the
government's mass housing program.
</P>
<P>
Estrada's agenda also involves the construction, management and
maintenance of low-cost housing by the private sector with the
government simply providing the seed capital and setting minimum
performance standards.
</P>
<P>
The administration will also propose several incentives,
including tax-free donations, to encourage the private sector and
non-government organizations to finance low-cost housing programs
and set up a mortgaged securities market. 
</P>
</TEXT>
