<HEADLINE> Major Chinese Cities Enjoy Good Air Quality </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 17 (Xinhua) -- The latest reports released by the
China Environmental Monitoring Center indicate that the country's
major cities continue to enjoy good air quality over the past week.
</P>
<P>
The quality levels can be attributed to the continuing
cloudiness, humidity and rainfall throughout China between July
10-16, according to the report.
</P>
<P>
Eleven cities, including Zhuhai and Xiamen, enjoyed excellent
air quality during the period.
</P>
<P>
Guangzhou's air quality improved significantly, with improving
levels also recorded for 28 other cities, including Shanghai,
Nanjing, Tianjin and Shenyang.
</P>
<P>
Six cities report low levels of air pollution, including
Beijing which recorded improving air quality in the previous
week. Major problems in the Chinese capital centered on nitrogen
oxide levels, while five other cities reported high levels of
suspended particles.
</P>
<P>
Experts predict the continuing precipitation with further ease
of pollution problems. 
</P>
</TEXT>
