<HEADLINE> U.S. Trade Deficit Rose to Record High in May </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 17 (Xinhua) -- The U.S. trade deficit soared
to a record high of 15.75 billion U.S. dollars in May as the
lingering economic crisis in Asia brought U.S. exports down to the
lowest level in 15 months, the Commerce Department said Friday.
</P>
<P>
The trade deficit for May was 10.3 percent higher than the
April imbalance of 14.27 billion dollars, underscoring that the
fallout from Asia's currency crisis will be more severe for the
U.S. manufacturers and farmers than previously forecast. 
</P>
