close in Sydney Thursday of 62.78 U.S. cents.
</P>
<P>
Hopes that the Japanese government would introduce economic
reforms and tax cuts to lift the country out of recession filtered
through to the Australian dollar via the Japanese yen.
</P>
<P>
Australia's strong trade ties with Japan have kept the
Australian dollar linked to the Japanese currency recently. Japan
accounts for about 20 percent of Australia's total goods and
service export each year.
</P>
<P>
