<HEADLINE> Gold Price in Hong Kong Down </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 17 (Xinhua) -- The gold price in Hong Kong lost
5 HK dollars to close at 2,700 HK dollars a tael Friday, according
to Po Sang Bank, one of the major gold dealers in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
The gold price is equivalent to 292.51 U.S. dollars a troy
ounce, 0.57 U.S. dollar down from the previous close at Friday's
exchange rate of one U.S. dollar to 7.7481 HK dollars. 
</P>
