<HEADLINE> Fund-Raising Program for Children's Immunization Launched </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 17 (Xinhua) -- Sheraton Hotels China and the
United Nations Children's Fund (UNICEF) launched an immunization
program for children this afternoon in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
The program -- "Immunize Children" -- will raise funds to
support UNICEF immunization programs against measles,
tuberculosis, whooping cough, diptheria, tetanus and polio.
</P>
<P>
Guests staying in a Sheraton hotel in China will have the
opportunity to have UNICEF donations added to their bills.
</P>
<P>
The goal of the program is to raise one million US dollars
annually for Chinese children.
</P>
<P>
UNICEF immunization programs have helped China provide
vaccinations to protect 85 percent of urban children under the age
of 7 against the aforementioned diseases. 
</P>
</TEXT>
