<HEADLINE> Gunmen Kill 4 Taxi Passengers in South Africa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, July 17 (Xinhua) -- Gunmen shot dead four
minibus taxi passengers at Dududu on South Africa's Kwazulu-Natal
south coast Friday, South African Press Association (SAPA)
reported.
</P>
<P>
Four gunmen armed with AK-47 rifles, shortguns and 9-mm
pistols attacked the minibus, SAPA quoted a police spokesman as
saying.
</P>
<P>
The victims were three men and a woman. A three-month-old baby
who apparently sustained a gunshot wound to her right leg was
hospitalized.
</P>
<P>
The gunmen ordered the taxi driver and conductor to leave
before killing the passengers, SAPA said.
</P>
<P>
The attack occurred at about 7 a.m. (0500 GMT), and the
deceased had not been identified. 
</P>
</TEXT>
