<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Traffic Accidents Rise in Ethiopia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, July 17 (Xinhua) -- About 100,000 traffic related
court cases in Addis Ababa have been settled during the past five
months, the Ethiopian Herald reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
Mesfin Adise, president of Addis Ababa courts for traffic
related cases, told the press that the cases under consideration
were from last January 20 to July 8.
</P>
<P>
Mesfin disclosed that the total fines amounted to two million
Birr (about 285,714 US Dollars) with the offenders having been
fined from between 10 to 200 Birr (1.4 to 28.57 US Dollars).
</P>
<P>
He explained that the number of cases within a short period of
five months indicates a very high rate of traffic-related
offences in the country.
</P>
<P>
The establishment of the urban traffic courts has played a
major role in easing the load of work of the federal courts and
federal first instance courts.
</P>
<P>
Referring to the new traffic regulation, he said, traffic
fines are imposed by the regional transport and communications
bureaux concerned and only in case of complaint can this be
considered by the traffic courts.
</P>
<P>
According to Addis Ababa transport and communications
authority, about 500 drivers in Addis Ababa trespass traffic
rules and regulation daily and an average 700 car accidents are
registered each month.
</P>
<P>
Some 531 persons lost their lives in car accidents in the past
two years in the city, 2,514 others sustained injuries and
properties worth over 2.8 million US Dollars were damaged.
</P>
<P>
The Addis Ababa city administration introduced recently a new
traffic regulation to contain traffic irregularities in the city.
</P>
</TEXT>
