<HEADLINE> Xi'an To Open Tourist Train To Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, July 17 (Xinhua) -- People in the ancient Chinese
capital of Xi'an will have a chance to travel to Hong Kong for a
five-day tour on a special train.
</P>
<P>
The "Chang'an Pearl" express train is scheduled to set out from
Xi'an, the capital of Shaanxi Province, on August 15, and arrive
in Hong Kong on August 17.
</P>
<P>
The train has 16 air-conditioned hard sleeper cars and one soft
sleeper car and can carry over 600 passengers.
</P>
<P>
It was sponsored by the Xi'an Branch of China International
Travel Service and two local travel agencies.  
</P>
</TEXT>
