<HEADLINE> New Zealand Stocks Finish Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, July 17 (Xinhua) -- The New Zealand sharemarket was
busy
Friday boosted by the record level reached on Wall Street
overnight.
</P>
<P>
The NZSE40 Index ended 40 points higher at 2172 with a turnover
of
131.88 million NZ dollars (68.6 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Air New Zealand went up 7 cents to 192 cents. AMP soared 26
cents to
2328 cents. Fletcher Energy edged up 2 cents to 579 cents. Lion
Nathan
jumped 12 cents to 480 cents. Telecom lifted 10 cents to 848
cents.
Carter Holt Harvey went up 11 cents to 235 cents. Fletcher
Building
increased 10 cents to 325 cents.
</P>
<P>
Overall, there were 84 rises and 32 falls. 
</P>
