<HEADLINE> Cook Islands Prime Minister to Visit NZ </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, July 17 (Xinhua) -- New Zealand Prime Minister
Jenny
Shipley announced here Friday that Cook Islands Prime Minister
Geoffrey
Henry will pay a visit to New Zealand next week.
</P>
<P>
Geoffrey Henry is currently chair of the South Pacific Forum.
In her
announcement, the New Zealand prime minister said: "We welcome his
visit
to New Zealand as an opportunity to discuss regional as well as
bilateral
questions ahead of next month's South Pacific Forum meeting of
heads of
government."
</P>
<P>
New Zealand's relations with the Cook Islands is one of this
country's
most important in the South Pacific region, she said, adding that
the two
countries share a special relationship and Cook Island Maori and
New
Zealand Maori have common ancestors.
</P>
<P>
Mrs Shipley said that while relations between New Zealand and
the Cook
Islands had been through some difficulties in recent years,
Geoffrey
Henry's upcoming visit would mark a new chapter in the
relationship.
</P>
<P>
The New Zealand prime minister said that her country would do
its
utmost to support the Cook Islands' economic reforms. 
</P>
</TEXT>
