<DOCNO> XIE19980717.0130 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tanzania Presses on with Building First Mining </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, July 17 (Xinhua) - The Tanzanian government has
allocated more than one billion shilings (about 1.52 million U.S.
Dollars) to boost the construction of its first mining college to
meet a crying need by the growing mining sector for professionals.
</P>
<P>
The college principal Joshua Kilebuka was quoted Friday by
local media as saying that the college, on the outskirts of
central Dodoma city, will open next year.
</P>
<P>
Kilebuka said the college is expected to train indigenous
mining experts not only for the growing small scale gemstone
mining sector, but also for the big new mining companies which
need local manpower.
</P>
<P>
"The college will train 40 full technician course graduates
annually at both diploma and certificate levels," he said. "It
will also offer short courses, researches and workshops for
miners."
</P>
<P>
The construction of the college comes in the wake of an
upsurge in mining over the last decade following liberalization
of the sector.
</P>
<P>
A report from the Ministry of Minerals and Energy estimates
that the small scale miners produce about 99 percent of the
country's total gemstone output, but they are in "critical
shortage of mining professionals".
</P>
<P>
Tanzania has a total of about 200 geologists, 54 mining and
processing engineers and 156 geological field technicians.
</P>
<P>
More than 100 miners were entombed in the rain-hit Mererani
Tanzanite mines in northern Arusha region in April this year due
to the lack of basic safety technology.
</P>
<P>
Deputy Minister for Minerals and Energy Manju Msambya said
that his ministry is trying to get money from donors to
facilitate the construction of the college and to recruit
competent mining tutors to ensure the quality of trainees.
</P>
<P>
A report by the Bank of Tanzania, the central bank, for the
1996/97 fiscal year indicates that the mineral exports earned
67.1 million U. S. Dollars, accounting for seven percent of the
total export earnings. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
