<HEADLINE> French Minister to Visit Nigeria </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, July 17 (Xinhua) -- French Cooperation Minister Charles
Josselin is to visit Nigeria in the next few days to make contact
with the country's new leader Abdulsalam Abubakar.
</P>
<P>
French Minister for Parliamentary Relations Daniel Vaillant
made the announcement Wednesday during a weekly meeting of the
French cabinet, the local Nigerian media reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
Vaillant described the visit of Josselin to Nigeria as
"political and diplomatic."
</P>
<P>
Josselin's coming visit is the latest in a series by Western
countries trying to encourage General Abubakar in his commitment
to continuing Nigeria's transition to democratic civilian rule.
</P>
<P>
British Junior Foreign Office Minister Tony Lloyd and the U.S.
Undersecretary for Political Affairs, Thomas Pickering, have
visited Nigeria earlier.
</P>
<P>
A statement from the French Foreign Ministry said that the
government has confidence in General Abubakar's resolve to
oversee the transition to democratic rule, in which the country's
main political forces would have a say.
</P>
<P>
Previously, "there was a risk that elections would go ahead
with a single candidate, but today, things are more open, a real
democratic transition is underway," the statement said.
</P>
<P>
"The international community has reacted positively to these
changes, which now must be reinforced and followed through," it
added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
