<HEADLINE> Road Connecting Ethiopia, Djibouti Under </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, July 17 (Xinhua) -- The Ethiopian Road Authority
said that the Dire Dawa-Dewele Road that connects Djibouti and
Ethiopia is under construction.
</P>
<P>
A local newspaper report Friday quoted Debebe Gizaw, Head of Public
Relations of the Ethiopian Road Authority, as saying that the
road which had been used by small vehicles until recently is now
crowded by about 700 heavy vehicles.
</P>
<P>
The increase in traffic is due to the increased use of the
Djibouti Port by Ethiopia following its border dispute with
Eritrea.
</P>
<P>
After the outbreak of Ethio-Eritrea border dispute in May,
Ethiopia has diverted from Assab Port of Eritrea to the port of
Djibouti as its outlet. About 300 Ethiopian trucks are
moving 6,000 tons a day through Djibouti, said an Ethiopian
government spokesperson in an earlier statement. 
</P>
</TEXT>
