<HEADLINE> Tanzanian State Company plans to Supply Reliable </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, July 17 (Xinhua) -- Tanzanian State Power
Company plans to provide electricity to major towns and tourist
attractions in the northern regions of Arusha and Kilimanjaro by
the year 2000.
</P>
<P>
The projects will be financed by the African Development Bank
(ADB) and the Nordic Development Fund (NDF), the Daily News
Friday quoted Alhaj Aboud Maalim, Board Chairman of the Tanzania
Electric Supply Company (TANESCO), as saying.
</P>
<P>
ADB will provide 43.3 million U.S. Dollars while the state
will grant seven billion Shillings (about 10.5 million U.S.
Dollars) for the program, Maalim said, adding that the NDF has
already provided five million U.S. Dollars.
</P>
<P>
The board chairman was briefing President Benjamin Mkapa on
the company's blueprint in Arusha.
</P>
<P>
"All principal towns of Kiteto, Mbulu and Karatu will be
provided with reliable power supply and the small town of Mto wa
Mbu and the Lake Manyara and Ngorongoro crater tourist hotels
will be supplied with electricity," Maalim was quoted by the
paper as saying.
</P>
<P>
He said that TANESCO will use environment-friendly equipment
called "aerial bound conductors (ABC) in the project to avoid
deforestation. 
</P>
