<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Field Mice: Deadly Virus Carrier </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, July 17 (Xinhua)-- Swedish researchers have found
that the harmless-looking field mouse can be carrying a deadly
virus.
</P>
<P>
They suspect the rodent spreads a virus that causes
myocarditis, a serious infection of the cardiac muscle. Over a
dozen Swedish die from this disease yearly.
</P>
<P>
The theory about the field mice' potential danger arose after
six young Swedish orienteers died of myocarditis in early 1990.
</P>
<P>
Bo Niklasson, a professor of virology at the Institute of
Protection Against Infectious Diseases, said that while they have
established the link between the rodent and the disease, they
have yet to nail down how the virus is spread.
</P>
<P>
"It would be wise for parents to keep small children away from
the rodent," he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
