<HEADLINE> Anshan Iron &AMP; Steel Company to Use U.S. Equipment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 17 (Xinhua) -- The Anshan Iron and Steel Group
(Angang) in northeast China's Liaoning Province will use automatic
control and transmission systems from the U.S. Rockwell Automation
Company for its two new continuous casting production lines.
</P>
<P>
The two lines are scheduled begin operating next year and will
have an annual production capacity of 1.1 million tons of
first-class slab ingots and 700,000 tons of four-strand blooms.
</P>
<P>
The installation of the two lines is expected to help the group
raise its continuous casting ratio, which is a key index in
measuring production efficiency in the iron and steel industry,
from the current 40 percent to 70 percent.
</P>
<P>
The group sees the renovation project as an aid to raising its
continuous casting ratio.
</P>
<P>
Rockwell Automotion will provide a unique package of services
to Angang, including programmable controllers, transmission
systems, PCs, and other devices. It has provided equipment for the
Baoshan Iron and Steel Company in Shanghai and Wuhan Iron and
Steel Company in central China.
</P>
<P>
In China's industrial automation market, Rockwell Automation
competes with other U.S. companies and the German Siemens Company.
</P>
<P>
With the installation of another two new continuous casting
production lines, Angang expects to increase its continuous
casting ratio to more than 90 percent before the year 2000.
</P>
<P>
Rockwell is a global electronic controls and communications
company with a leading position in industrial automation,
avionics, and electronics. In China, the company focuses its
investment in industrial automation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
