<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, July 17 (Xinhua) -- Philippine President Joseph Estrada
will ask the 11th Congress, which opens its regular session on
July 27, to give priority to his proposal to place the entire
country under a comprehensive land use program.
</P>
<P>
Estrada said in a news release Friday that in line with his
objective, there is an urgent need for a comprehensive national
land use program to preserve rural areas earmarked for food
products.
</P>
<P>
In his scheduled first State of the Nation Address on July 27,
Estrada is expected to propose an integrated Land Use Act, which
he believes will curb the irrational conversion of prime
agricultural lands into industrial parks, resorts with golfing
courses and housing subdivisions.
</P>
<P>
Estrada has called for a stop to the "irrational conversion" of
prime agricultural lands that has put the Comprehensive Agrarian
Reform Program in jeopardy and has been partly responsible for the
country's shrinking farm productivity. 
