<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE>   Worldwide Wafer Fabrication Equipment Market Sluggish </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LOS ANGELES, July 16 (Xinhua) -- The worldwide wafer
fabrication equipment market continues to be sluggish this year,
with revenue forecast to reach 16.7 billion U.S. dollars, down 17
percent from 1997, said Dataquest Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. California-based market research firm also forecast
that the market will have a smooth growth at 2.9 percent in
1999. But the firm's analysts said that the industry will achieve
a big boom in 2000 and 2001.
</P>
<P>
The next six months will be extremely difficult in the market
because of oversupply. "Aggressive investment in 0.25-micron
technology throughout 1997 contributed to the continuing
overcapacity in the industry," Dataquest said in a report. "The
economic slowdown in Asia and Japan has made the 1998 spending
environment downright ugly."
</P>
<P>
But Dataquest analysts forecast a spending boom during
2000-2001, with a shortage of dynamic random access memory (DRAM)
emerging early in 2000. The worldwide wafer fabrication equipment
market will grow 37 percent in 2000 and 49.8 percent in 2001.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
