<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Pakistani PM Leaves for Colombo July 28 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, July 17 (Xinhua) -- Pakistani Prime Minister Nawaz
Sharif will leave for Colombo on July 28 to attend the 10th SAARC
summit which will provide the first occasion for a meeting between
Pakistani and Indian leaders after the May nuclear tests, the APP
reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
Bangladesh, Bhutan, India, Maldives, Nepal, Pakistan and host
Sri Lanka will take part in the seven-nation South Asian
Association for Regional Cooperation (SAARC) summit to be held
from July 29 to 31.
</P>
<P>
Analysts say a meeting between Prime Minister Nawaz Sharif and
his Indian counterpart Atal Behari Vajpayee in Colombo may help
cool down the tension in South Asia, said the report by the
official Associated Press of Pakistan (APP).
</P>
<P>
This should help the two countries resume talks at the foreign
secretary level to address outstanding issues including Kashmir,
the APP said.
</P>
<P>
Pak-Indian foreign secretaries' talks met a stalemate in the
third round in New Delhi last September. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
