<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Brisbane Hopes to Host 2001 Goodwill Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBEERA, July 17 (Xinhua) -- Australian sports officials are
hoping to host the 2001 Goodwill Games, according to reports from
Sydney.
</P>
<P>
An Australian state government minister flew to New York on
Friday to try to persuade Games founder Ted Turner to take the
multi-sport extravaganza to Brisbane in 2001.
</P>
<P>
Brisbane hosted the 1982 Commonwealth Games and was nominated
for the 1992 Summer Olympics.
</P>
<P>
"We're optimistic but still there's no decision," said a
spokesman for Queensland state sports minister Bob Gibbs. "If we
won it, it would be an enormous benefit for Queensland."
</P>
<P>
The Goodwill Games were founded by Turner in 1986. The first
four venues alternated in Russia and the United States. But Turner
wants to take the Games somewhere else.
</P>
<P>
The announcement of the new site is expected on Saturday.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980717.0170 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai Securities Trading Down In First Half </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 17 (Xinhua) -- Trading on the Shanghai Stock
Exchange (SSE) was down 10 percent at 1.65 trillion yuan in the
first half of this year, the exchange announced today.
</P>
<P>
The composite stock index, however, took an upturn during the
period, opening at 1,200.95 at the beginning of the year and
closing at 1,339.20 at the end of June.
</P>
<P>
The index hit a high of 1,422.98 and a low of 1,110.09 during
the six-month period.
</P>
<P>
At the end of June, the SSE had 493 securities listed, with 456
A shares for domestic investors, and 52 B shares for foreign
investors. It also had 18 investment funds, 15 treasury bonds, and
4 company bonds.
</P>
<P>
Turnover of stocks was 698 billion yuan in the first six
months, treasures bonds came to 922 billion yuan and investment
funds, 31.5 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
Thirty-four companies were listed during the period. These
included such large state-owned companies as Hongqiao Airport,
Handan Iron and Steel Complex, and ther Qilu Petrochemical
Works.
</P>
<P>
These companies and the Jintai, Xinghua and Anxin investment
funds have increased the exchange's capitalization to 124 billion
shares, up 40 percent on an annual basis.
</P>
<P>
Some 33.7 billion shares with a total capitalization of 1.15
trillion yuan are in circulation.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai securities market, which now has 18.9 million
investors, raised 24.6 billion yuan in funds in the first half.
</P>
</TEXT>
