<HEADLINE> Chinese Scientists Invent New Medical Adhesive </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, July 17 (Xinhua) -- Chinese scientists have developed a
kind of fast-acting glue that can be used during surgery as
adhesive for cut edges and doctors are claiming that the super
glue can replace traditional sutures.
</P>
<P>
The adhesive was invented by Chen Tiyi and other colleagues
following 14 years of research.
</P>
<P>
The adhesive substance will be available on the market soon. It
can bind two cut surfaces together less than 14 seconds after it
is spread along them.
</P>
<P>
The patented surgical adhesive's easy use and ability to stop
bleeding and relieve pain was confirmed by the General Hospital of
the People's Liberation Army and several other hospitals.
</P>
<P>
It is being produced by Beijing's Shunkang Science and
Technology Corporation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
