<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Nationwide Anti-Polio Campaign Launched in Kenya </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, July 17 (Xinhua) -- A nationwide anti-polio campaign
has been launched in Kenya with more than five million children
under the age of five projected to be injected with polio
vaccine.
</P>
<P>
Kenyan Health Minister Jackson Kalweo made the announcement at
the launch of the 1998 national immunization campaign Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The children will be given two doses of the oral polio
vaccine regardless of their immunization status, the East African
Standard newspaper Friday quoted Kalweo as saying.
</P>
<P>
Special strategies and measures have been taken to
increase accessibility to vaccination stations, the minister said,
stressing that the success of the campaign depends
on proper and efficient organizing and mass mobilization.
</P>
<P>
"Two strategies will be used, namely fixed vaccination posts
at the usual health facilities and mobile teams in hard-to-reach
populations," Kalweo said.
</P>
<P>
A total of 8,000 posts have been set up across the east
African country in population-concentrated areas like market
places, schools, churches and railway stations, said the Kenyan
minister said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
