<HEADLINE> Ronaldo Denies He had Pre-Cup Convulsion </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRASILIA, July 16 (Xinhua) -- Brazilian striker Ronaldo
appeared on Thursday and said he had not suffered an epileptic
convulsion hours before World Cup final, according to a newswire
from Sao Paulo.
</P>
<P>
"Nothing happened. There was never something like that,"
Ronaldo was quoted by Agencia Estado.
</P>
<P>
"The problem is that the whole team played badly and they found
a reason for the defeat in me," 21-year-old Ronaldo said.
</P>
<P>
But Ronaldo earlier told local television that he had feared
for his life after the mysterious convulsion.
</P>
<P>
He was not satisfied with the contradicting reports about his
health.
</P>
<P>
Ronaldo had been secluded after returning from France and was
reported to have been taking a holiday with his family. 
</P>
