<HEADLINE> Investment In China's Tianjin Increases </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, July 17 (Xinhua) -- In the first half of the year, the
northern Chinese port city of Tianjin added 470 overseas-funded
projects worth nearly 2.37 billion U.S. dollars, nearly 1.94
billion dollars of which come from overseas.
</P>
<P>
The projects include 53 with more than 5 million U.S. dollars
of investment each and 49 with more than 10 million dollars each.
</P>
<P>
The city had 34 Sino-foreign cooperative projects and 329
projects owned solely by foreigners, or 30 percent and 4.8 percent
more than the figures in the same 1997 period.
</P>
<P>
The number of infrastructure projects is on the rise, with 558
million U.S. dollars of overseas investment for 26 transportation
projects in the six-month period.
</P>
<P>
The existing 123 overseas-funded enterprises added 345 million
dollars of investment during the first half, a 15 percent increase
from the same 1997 period.
</P>
<P>
Tianjin has been a leader among northern Chinese cities in amount
of overseas investment. It had had more than 11,600 overseas-funded
enterprises by the end of last year, using nearly 20 billion U.S.
dollars in overseas investment. 
</P>
</TEXT>
