<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Flood Situation Deteriorating in Bangladesh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, July 17 (Xinhua) -- The flood situation in Bangladesh
deteriorated further with fresh areas inundated in different
districts, said press reports reaching here Friday.
</P>
<P>
Water levels of most major rivers continue to rise aggravating
the flood situation in 17 districts out of the total 64 districts
in the country.
</P>
<P>
Major rivers in the four basins are still flowing above their
danger marks, and the Brahmaputra river is flowing 10, 32, 46
centimeters above the danger level at three places, according to
the Flood Information Center.
</P>
<P>
Over 2 million people have been affected, more than 400,000
hectares of cropland have been inundated, and at least 33 people
have died in the flood, reports said.
</P>
<P>
Prime Minister Sheikh Hasina has directed all the departments
concerned to take all necessary measures to combat the flood and
do a good job of relief work.
</P>
<P>
Disaster management and relief minister and the affected
districts' governments have sanctioned grants as emergency relief,
and at the same time they have started to implement the plans to
evacuate the flood-affected people.
</P>
<P>
The period from July to October is the monsoon season in this
South Asian country, during which there are always heavy rains
causing serious floods. 
</P>
</TEXT>
