<BODY>
<HEADLINE> India Works on Vertically Launched Missile </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, July 17 (Xinhua) -- The Indian navy has begun work
on a vertically launched surface-to-air missile, Trishul, with
enhanced engagement and quick reaction capability, The Hindustan
Times quoted highly placed sources as saying here Friday.
</P>
<P>
The decision to change the configuration from the existing
horizontal configuration was taken after it was found that
precious reaction time could be saved in this mode, the paper
said.
</P>
<P>
The new configuration ensures that the missile can be used in
surface-to-air and anti-missile role in the same position, it
added.
</P>
<P>
Trishul missile, which has a range of nine kilometers, is part
of the Integrated Guided Missile Program in India.
</P>
<P>
The existing version of the missile is under flight trial in
the user configuration mode.
</P>
<P>
The naval version was flight-tested on June 3. This was the
first development flight-test of the missile in a series before it
would be offered for user trials, the paper said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980717.0209 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Economy Grows Seven Percent in First Six Months (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 17 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese economy grew seven
percent year-on-year in the first half of this year, the State
Statistics Bureau (SSB) announced here today.
</P>
<P>
The Gross Domestic Product (GDP) totaled 3.4731 trillion yuan
during the January-June period, up seven percent, Ye Zhen, the
bureau's spokesman, told a press conference here this morning.
</P>
<P>
Overall speaking, it is not easy for China to maintain stable
economic growth under the situation of increasing pressure of the
Asian financial crisis, insufficient domestic demand and serious
natural disasters, Ye told the press conference.
</P>
<P>
"And this only indicates that the policies and measures taken
by the Chinese government are utterly correct and effective," he
said.
</P>
<P>
Though the growth rate is one percentage point lower than the
projected economic growth target for the whole of 1998, Ye said
the goal is attainable.
</P>
<P>
"So long as the polices to boost domestic demand are earnestly
followed in the second half of this year, China's economic growth
will pick up and this year's eight percent growth target can be
realized," he said.
</P>
<P>
Qiu Xiaohua, SSB's chief economist, explained at the same
conference that China's investment growth rate has been rising
this year, up from around 10 percent year-on-year in the first
quarter to 15 percent in the second quarter and 16.3 percent in
June.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, he noted, Chinese banks have also increased and
accelerated the extension of loans to spur economic growth.
</P>
<P>
"Effective rise in investment and bank loans heralds an
economic recovery, which is already in sight," Qiu said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980717.0210 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Economy Grows Seven Percent in First Six Months (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Ye went on to say that China's price level remained low in the
first half of this year, with the retail price index falling 2.1
percent and the consumer price index, which covers the costs of
both goods and services, inching down 0.3 percent.
</P>
<P>
SSB statistics also show that China's foreign trade was valued
at 151.4 billion US dollars in the first half, up 5.2 percent from
a year ago. Exports rose 7.6 percent to 87 billion US dollars
whereas imports was up 2.2 percent to 64.4 billion US dollars,
leaving a half-year trade surplus of 22.6 billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Between January and June, contractual overseas direct investment
in China totaled 24.2 billion US dollars in the first half of this
year, up 5.5 percent year-on-year. Paid-in overseas direct
investment, however, edged down 1.3 percent to 20.5 billion US
dollars.
</P>
<P>
China's industrial incremental value grew 7.9 percent to 920.9
billion yuan in the six-month period. But combined profits of
state-owned industrial firms plunged 49.5 percent to 25.7 billion
yuan in the first five months.
</P>
<P>
China's summer grain output, meanwhile, declined by 11 percent
to 113.1 billion kg, or 14.6 billion kg less than the comparable
figure of last year, when China reported a good summer grain
harvest.
</P>
<P>
Ye acknowledged that China's investment in fixed assets totaled
582.8 billion yuan in the first six months, up 13.8 percent from
the same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, China's balance of international payments remained
sound during the first half of this year, with foreign exchange
reserves on steady rise and the exchange rate of the Renminbi yuan
stable, the spokesman said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
