<HEADLINE> Plavsic Enraged by Schumacher's Threatening on Serbs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, July 16 (Xinhua) -- Bosnian Serb Republic President
Biljan Plavsic has threatened to cut contact with a senior
international representative in Bosnia who said that the necks of
many Bosnian Serbs should be "twisted."
</P>
<P>
In a Sarajevo-based newspaper, Hanns Schumacher, Deputy High
Representative of the Peace Implementation Council, criticized the
Republic Srpska for failing to carry out the repatriation of
refugees and threatened to impose sanctions against the republic.
</P>
<P>
Schumacher, a German, said that the necks of many Bosnian Serbs
should be twisted, reported the Yugoslav Tanjug news agency.
</P>
<P>
Plavsic said that the Germans must know that more than a
million Serbs were killed by the German fascists by decapitation
during World War II.
</P>
<P>
She added Bosnian Serbs would never allow anyone to threaten to
twist the necks of Serbs in their own territory.
</P>
<P>
The enraged president said that she didn't know if she would
continue to deal with Schumacher. 
</P>
</TEXT>
