<HEADLINE> Austria Welcomes Brazil Signing Nuclear Ban Treaties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, July 16 (Xinhua) -- Austrian Foreign Minister Wolfgang
Schussel has welcomed Brazil's ratification of the two treaties
banning nuclear tests and proliferation of nuclear weapons.
</P>
<P>
Schussel, speaking as the executive president of the Council of
Ministers of the European Union, said Brazil would strengthen its
key role as one of the major powers in the field of nuclear
disarmament by signing the Comprehensive Test Ban Treaty (CTBT)
and the Nuclear Non-Proliferation Treaty (NPT).
</P>
<P>
He stressed that Brazil had joined forces with other countries
in putting an end to nuclear arms and that the ratification came
at a critical moment for the international community after a
series of nuclear tests conducted in South Asia.
</P>
<P>
Brazil is among the few countries with the technological
capacity to build atomic bombs.
</P>
<P>
Brazilian President Fernando Henrique Cardoso signed the
treaties on July 13 in a ceremony attended by UN Secretary-General
Kofi Annan.
</P>
<P>
Annan called the Brazilian move "a gift for future generations
that should be followed by other nations".
</P>
<P>
U.S. President Bill Clinton said Brazil's decision renewed
momentum for the international community to halt the spread of
nuclear weapons and promote disarmament around the world.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
