<HEADLINE> European Countries Prepare for Possible Kosovo Refugee Tide </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, July 16 (Xinhua) -- Interior ministers of five European
countries Thursday discussed measures for stemming the anticipated
exodus of Kosovo refugees.
</P>
<P>
The ministers from Austria, Germany, Switzerland, France and
Italy agreed in their meeting here that a peaceful solution to the
Kosovo crisis is the only way to prevent the ethnic Albanian
refugees from swarming to the neighboring and other European
countries.
</P>
<P>
They also reached consensus on the need for funding the
building of refugee shelters in northern Albania and Macedonia.
</P>
<P>
Ministers of France and Germany also called on Yugoslav
President Slobodan Milosevic to put back in place and keep to the
autonomy of Kosovo to avoid another civil war and the resulting
refugee tide.
</P>
<P>
Karl Schloegl, interior minister of Austria, proposed that EU
provide money aid to members worst hit by the anticipated refugee
tide. 
