<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Myanmar NGOs Active in Social, Health Sectors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, July 17 (Xinhua)-- Myanmar's nongovernmental
organizations (NGOs) are playing an active role in the promotive
activities of the country's social and health sectors with the
support of the government, becoming more multi-faceted and more
widespread.
</P>
<P>
A new NGO, the Myanmar Anti-Narcotic Association, has been
formed with the Myanmar Red Cross Society strengthened, Minister
of Health Major General Ket Sein was quoted by Friday's the New
Light of Myanmar newspaper as saying.
</P>
<P>
At a two-day review meeting of Myanmar's NGOs, which began
Thursday, Ket Sein disclosed that nine international NGOs have
initiated memorandums of understanding (MOUs) with the Myanmar
Ministry of Health and a greater number of such other
organizations have submitted their protocols for future programs
with the ministry to reach more MOUs.
</P>
<P>
Myanmar is not only cooperating with NGOs in the country in
primary health care and disease control programs but also
cooperating with United Nations agencies and other social
organizations to get the optimum health care for the citizens.
</P>
<P>
However, the minister warned against copying styles of other
countries in the implementation of some action programs to avoid
delay.
</P>
<P>
He also called for initiating joint TB/HIV programs in Myanmar
to improve the health status of the people.
</P>
<P>
In order to achieve the goals of the five-year National Health
Plan (1996-2001), the Myanmar Ministry of Health has laid down two
main objectives -- to enable every citizen to attain full life
expectancy and enjoy longevity, and to ensure every citizen is
free from diseases.
</P>
<P>
The three strategies that have been adopted to achieve these
objectives include widespread dissemination of health information
and education to reach rural areas and grassroots levels,
enhancing disease prevention activities, and providing adequate
treatment to prevailing diseases. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
