<HEADLINE> Chinese Economist Calls for Intensified Investment to Stimulate Economy(2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 17 (Xinhua) -- Another way for the economy to
pick up is to actively increase consumption demand, especially the
demand in rural areas, said Wang Guogang.
</P>
<P>
The economist further suggested that the government not only
increase investment in infrastructure, but also intensify input
in the upgrading of enterprise fixed-assets.
</P>
<P>
The fastest investment growth during the first half year was
registered in the infrastructure sector. For instance, investment
in transportation and telecommunications, grew 32.4 percent,
compared with the average fixed asset investment growth of 13.8
percent.
</P>
<P>
Wang pointed out that intensified investment effort does not
necessarily mean massive extension of bank loans, which can easily
give rise to bad loans and pose severe burden on the banks and
projects as was the case during the 1980s.
</P>
<P>
According to statistics released today by the State Statistic
Bureau, the first six months have already seen an upward trend in
the growth of fix asset investment, and the growth rate during
this period was 3.5 percentage points higher than that of the
first quarter. 
</P>
