<HEADLINE> Economist Calls for Intensified Investment to Stimulate Economy(1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 17 (Xinhua) -- A leading Chinese economist
suggested today that an investment growth of between 15 percent
and 18 percent is needed to stimulate the country's economy in the
remaining months of the year.
</P>
<P>
China's economy slowed down to seven percent during the
January-June period from the 8.8 percent of the previous year,
according to the statistics released by the State Statistics
Bureau today.
</P>
<P>
Commenting on the current economic growth pace, Wang Guogang,
deputy director of the Finance and Trade Center of the Chinese
Academy of Social Sciences, said that the economy still faces
servere challenges if it is to meet the yearly growth target of
eight percent, and intensified investment is necessary to achieve
that goal.
</P>
</TEXT>
