<HEADLINE> Cipollini Wins First Victory Since Tour de France Began </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 16 (Xinhua) -- Italian Mario Cipollini broke
through his Tour de France misfortunes with winning
228.5-kilometer fifth stage from Cholet to Chateauroux on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Cipollini clocked five hours 18 minutes 49 seconds.
</P>
<P>
German Erik Zabel finished second and Frenchman Christophe
Mengin was third with an indentical time.
</P>
<P>
Australian Stuart O'Grady kept his overall lead with a time of
25 hours two minutes 18 seconds. American George Hincapie came
second with seven seconds behind followed by Bo Hamburger of
Denmark, 11 seconds behind the leader. 
</P>
