<HEADLINE> China's Fixed Asset Investment Reaches Peak in June </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 17 (Xinhua) -- China's investment in state-owned
fixed assets grew to the highest point at 16.3 percent in June on
a monthly basis, according to figures released by the State
Statistics Bureau (SSB) today.
</P>
<P>
SSB spokesman Ye Zhen said investment in fixed assets of the
state-owned sector reached 582.8 billion yuan (70.2 billion US
dollars) in the first six months, up 13.8 percent
year-on-year. The figure was 3.5 percentage points higher than
that of the first three month period.
</P>
<P>
The structure of fixed asset investment continued to improve
during the January-June period. Investment in agriculture
increased by 16.1 percent and that in transport and
post-telecommunications 32.4 percent, compared with the same
period of last year. Investment in these two sectors gained 3.1
percentage points in its ratio against the total investment figure
over the same period of last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
