<HEADLINE> China to Repair Historical Party Site </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 17 (Xinhua) -- China will repair a historical
site of the Communist Party of China to carry on its revolutionary
legacy.
</P>
<P>
The Publications Bureau of the Chinese Soviet's temporary
central government, located in Ruijin of east China's Jiangxi
province, pioneered the Party's publications efforts in 1931.
</P>
<P>
Many of the important documents of the Chinese Soviet Republic
were published by the bureau, said a spokesman for the Press and
Publications Administration.
</P>
<P>
The bureau's rundown old building covers 500 square meters and
is in danger of collapsing at any time. The renovation will
restore its original appearance, and many artifacts will be added
to its exhibition hall.
</P>
<P>
More than 140 publishing houses and administrative departments
have donated money to repair the site, and the work is expected to
be completed in the first half of next year.
</P>
<P>
The CPC was founded in 1921, and set up its first temporary
government in Ruijin in 1931 after staging several uprisings. The
Ruijin government existed until 1934 when the Red Army began its
famous Long March to northwest China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
