<HEADLINE> Yugoslavia's Industry Output Grows </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, July 16 (Xinhua) -- Yugoslavia's industry output in
the first six months of this year expanded by 11.7 percent over
the same period of last year, the Federal Statistical Bureau (FSB)
said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The building materials sector in the recent six months
increased by 25.2 percent while the sectors of textiles, leather,
rubber and papermaking each rose by 21.7 percent.
</P>
<P>
The metal processing and electronics industries grew by 16.2
percent, metallurgy by 13.7 percent, timber processing by 10
percent, and food and tobacco by 7.7 percent, the FSB said.
</P>
<P>
Boosted by expanding industry, exports in the six months
reached 1.152 billion U.S. dollars, up seven percent over the same
period of last year, and imports were 2.385 billion U.S. dollars,
up 4.5 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
