<HEADLINE> Bulgaria Will Not Have Official Contact with Taiwan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, July 16 (Xinhua) -- Bulgarian Prime Minister Ivan Kostov
has said that his government will honor its pledge not to have
official contact with Taiwan as it maintains the "one China"
policy.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with Xinhua, Kostov said Bulgaria recognized
that Taiwan was an inalienable part of the People's Republic of
China (PRC) and the PRC government was the sole legitimate
government of China.
</P>
<P>
Bulgarian President Petar Stoyanov signed a joint statement
with China during a visit in May, reaffirming Bulgaria's policy on
the Taiwan issue.
</P>
<P>
Some former Bulgarian diplomats, unhappy with the present
Taiwan policy of their government, said the signing of the joint
statement was a "mistake."
</P>
<P>
Kostov said that the joint statement signed between the two
countries was not a mistake at all and it reaffirmed the
long-standing policy adopted by the Bulgarian government on the
Taiwan issue. 
</P>
</TEXT>
