<HEADLINE> Sino-Russian Border Trade Increasing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARBIN, July 17 (Xinhua) -- Suifenhe City on the Sino-Russian
border in northeast China's Heilongjiang Province has had 530,000
Russian tourists in the past 6 years.
</P>
<P>
This is more than half the number of Russian tourists in
Heilongjiang during the period, and in the first six months of
this year, the number of Russian tourists in Suifenhe was up by 10
percent over the same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
The city has raised about a billion yuan for urban
infrastructural construction for Sino-Russian trade and tourism
since it was approved as an open city in 1992.
</P>
<P>
It can handle 6 million tons of freight and 1.5 million
passengers a year and the mobile phone service and direct dialing
and international direct dialing have brought this border city in
closer contact with the outside world.
</P>
<P>
It has also built tourist facilities for shopping, sightseeing,
and vacationing and has tourist routes to five Russian cities and
some major Chinese cities.
</P>
<P>
Suifenhe has 40 shops and markets specializing in Chinese
light industrial products and articles for daily use and has
strict inspections of commodities to prevent sub-standard goods
from getting into the stores.
</P>
<P>
About 600 million U.S. dollars worth of Chinese goods are sold
to Russia through the Suifenhe tourist trade alone annually.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
