<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Foreign Trade, Investment Continued to Grow in First Half </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 17 (Xinhua) -- China's foreign trade and overseas
investment sustained growth momentum during the first half of this
year, the State Statistic Bureau announced today.
</P>
<P>
Ye Zhen, the Bureau spokesman told a press conference held here
that the country's import and export value hit 151.4 billion US
dollars in the first half, up 5.2 percent year on year.
</P>
<P>
Of the total foreign trade, exports accounted for 87 billion
US dollars, a rise of 7.6 percent, while imports amounted to 64.4
billion US dollars, up 2.2 percents, with a trade surplus of
22.6 billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
In the first six months, the pledged overseas direct investment
was valued at 24.2 billion US dollars, an increase of 5.5 percent;
the overseas funds put into place reached 20.5 billion US dollars,
a drop of 1.3 percent.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman also told the conference that the half year also
witnessed a sound balance of international payment, the increase
of state foreign exchange reserves and a stablized exchange rate
of the Renminbi yuan against other major foreign currencies.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
