<HEADLINE> Zhuhai Real Estate Market Out of Doldrums </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHUHAI, July 17 (Xinhua) -- The real estate market in the
Zhuhai Special Economic Zone has come out of the doldrums into
brisk trading since the beginning of this year.
</P>
<P>
Housing transaction in this south China city in the first half
of the year reached 682,400 square meters totalling 1.887 billion
yuan (227.3 million U.S. dollars), soaring 151 and 138 percent
respectively over last year.
</P>
<P>
Property market analysts attribute the boom to an increasing
number of homebuyers from other cities attracted by Zhuhai's
beautiful natural environment. These buyers account for 60
percent of the homes and the bulk of the beach-side property sold
this year.
</P>
<P>
The boom has also been attributed to the availability of
diversified real estate suitable to both wage-earners and
businessmen. 
</P>
</TEXT>
