Xinhua Daily Telegraph
</P>
<P>
-- The railway traffic on a flood-damaged line in northwestern
China is expected to resume this afternoon and more than 14,000
passengers on 13 trains have been moved to other places.
</P>
<P>
On July 13, a 43-kilometer section of the railway line between
Lanzhou, the capital of Gansu Province and Urumqi, the capital of
Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region was damaged by torrential waters.
</P>
