<HEADLINE> Thailand's Exports Increase </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, July 17 (Xinhua) -- Thailand's exports rose by 62.4
percent in baht terms in the first six months of this year
compared with the same period last year, but the increase in
dollar terms was only 4.2 percent, according to figures prepared
by the Customs Department available Friday.
</P>
<P>
Thailand's exports in the first six months of this year totaled
1,175 billion baht or 26.9 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Exports in June totaled 192.58 billion baht, up 57.5 percent
from the same month last year, and up 15.5 percent from May. In
dollar terms, June exports totaled 4.65 billion U.S. dollars, down
2.4 percent from June 1997 but up 7.5 percent from May.
</P>
<P>
Imports in the first half year totaled 945.3 billion baht, an
increase of 5.3 percent. In dollar terms, total imports were 21.3
billion U.S. dollars, a decline of 38.2 percent.
</P>
<P>
Thailand had a trade surplus of 230.6 billion baht in the first
half year compared with a deficit of 173.7 billion baht for the
same period last year.
</P>
<P>
In dollar terms, the surplus was 5.6 billion U.S. dollars
compared with a 6.55-billion deficit in the first half of last
year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
