their respective responsible officials to provide full support.
(UN-Bosnia and Herzegovina-program)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- U.S. President Bill Clinton has planned to sign
papers authorizing a renewal of the waiver for another six months
of the Helms-Burton law that requires the United States to
penalize foreign firms investing in Cuba, the White House said on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Spokesman Mike McCurry said Clinton would sign the papers later
on Thursday. It will be the second time that Clinton is going to
waive the sanctions since he signed the legislation into law in
1996. (BC-US-Cuba-Sanctions Waiver)
</P>
