<HEADLINE> 15 Injured in Major Traffic Accident in Germany </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, July 16 (Xinhua) -- Fifteen people were injured, two of
them seriously, in a major traffic accident involving 14 vehicles
in the western German city of Dortmund Thursday evening, German
police said.
</P>
<P>
The accident occurred when a sand-loaded truck rammed into 12
passenger cars and a light truck waiting before a traffic light in
Dortmund.
</P>
<P>
Two of the cars were totally damaged with their drivers
seriously injured and still in critical conditions, police added.
</P>
<P>
Firefighters have already managed to put out a fire which broke
out due to the accident. 
</P>
