<DOCNO> XIE19980717.0291 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> World Bank Supports Kenya El Nino Emergency Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 16 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank approved here
Thursday a 40 million U.S. dollar fast-track interest-free credit
to Kenya to help mitigate the effects of flooding caused by the El
Nino phenomenon.
</P>
<P>
Kenya was struck by unusual rainstorms during the latter part
of 1997 and early 1998, which caused widespread devastation in the
East African nation. The government declared a state of emergency
in 23 districts, nearly one third of the country.
</P>
<P>
The project seeks to provide urgently needed resources to help
rehabilitate some of the devastated infrastructure in order to
restore normal social and economic activities to the people in the
affected areas.
</P>
<P>
The credit will be channeled through the International
Development Association, the World Bank's concessional lending
affiliate for developing countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
